- 'Dawn of 2020' refers to the start of the year 2020 (January 1, 2020);
- 'Touched by the hands of listeners' refers to the songs that have been accessed at least once.

- "energetic" refers to the highest tempo in the songs;
- "a duo of admirers" refers to at least 2 comments;
- "a single maestro" refers to at least 1 producer;
- "a solo artist" refers to at least 1 artist.

- 'in_progress' status refers to songs that are currently being worked on or produced;
- 'Hip Hop' is a genre of music;
- 'tempo' is the speed or pace of a song, measured in beats per minute (BPM);
- 'primary artist' refers to the artist with the highest percentage of ownership in the song.

- 'singer' refers to the artist's role in the song;
- 'primary producer' refers to the producer's role in the song;
- 'access count' represents the number of times a song has been accessed or played.

- "a couple" typically means 2 or more;
- "listed in descending order by song count" means the genres with the most songs appear first;
- "alphabetically by genre name" means that if two genres have the same number of songs, they are ordered by their names in alphabetical order.

- 'Primary producer' refers to the producer marked as primary in the `song_producers` table;
- 'Primary artist' refers to the artist with the highest percentage of ownership in the `song_artists` table;
- 'Most recently edited' means the song had its last access type as 'edit'.

